libjson++
------------------------------------------
A fast and intuitive C++ interface for handling JSON structures

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.15-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-3
  libstdc++6-4.5.3-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cmake-2.8.7-1
  cygport-0.10.10-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  gcc4-g++-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://git.cflinux.hu/?p=libjson.git

Canonical download:
  git://git.cflinux.hu/libjson.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libjson++-0.3.1+git20120514-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libjson++-0.3.1+git20120514-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libjson++-0.3.1+git20120514-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjson++-0.3.1+git20120514-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjson++0-0.3.1+git20120514-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjson++-devel-0.3.1+git20120514-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libjson++)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libjson++.README
  /usr/share/doc/libjson++/COPYING

(libjson++0)
  /usr/bin/cygjson++-0.dll

(libjson++-devel)
  /usr/include/json/iarray.hpp
  /usr/include/json/ibool.hpp
  /usr/include/json/inumeric.hpp
  /usr/include/json/iobject.hpp
  /usr/include/json/iscalar.hpp
  /usr/include/json/istring.hpp
  /usr/include/json/ivalue.hpp
  /usr/include/json/refcounted.hpp
  /usr/include/json/util.hpp
  /usr/include/json/value.hpp
  /usr/lib/libjson++.dll.a

------------------

